11 bMx Metagenomics / BIOINFORM / MetaSeqGB L'affaire se complique : la plateforme BNext de Applied Maths est la cible dès le départ: forte implication et modifications du contexte qui obligent à regarder en détails, se prémunir, re-dimensionner tout cela dans une fenêtre temporelle de siganture globale du contrat très contrainte
Few kw: React/Redux - Mono - Nginx - IIS, JQuery, D3, Bootstrap, Require.js, Grunt/Gulp, Bower, Lodash, Handlebars
Applied Maths : “ “For the front end, we would recommend to maximally make use of JavaScript, thus building up visualizations client-side using result data files served by the back end. The framework for this is based React/Redux. Php can be used for back-end / front end dialog. ”
HPC : “Applied Maths Calculation Engine (CE) installation. This service provides the gateway to the local grid scheduler (SGE/OGE/SonGE/Univa/HTCondor/Slurm/…).” The Calculation Engine is written in C++, is platform-independent and uses the DRMAA API to connect to the local grid scheduler (required version is DRMAA1.0).”
Applied Maths Download Manager (DM) “This service takes care of input files that have to be downloaded from NCBI, ENA…”; “It submits download jobs through the CE to the local grid scheduler, and keeps track of downloaded files for reuse and removal after expiration. The Download Manager also keeps a local cache of genomes that are processed on the Calculation Engine for efficient reuse. This component is written in Node.js.”
